        <title>Why does SPFE Open Toolkit use XML?</title>
        <byline>
            <author-name>John Farrell MacDonald</author-name>
        </byline>

        <precis> 
            <p> Standardized by the World Wide Web Consortium (W3C), the
                Extensible Markup Language (XML) has a rich body of
                technologies and tools that support it. Though the SPFE
                architecture could be implemented in other ways, XML was
                selected because of its robust set of tools and the fact that
                it is an open standard.</p> 
        </precis>

